  "text": "A duplex formed by annealing r(AGAUAGAGAUAUCUUAGGA-UCCGUUAAGU) and AGAACTTAACGGATCCTAAGAGATCTCT was used for measuring RNase activity. For DNase-exohelix and DNase I only the 2 mM CaCl 2 buffer was used. The RNA strand was synthesized and purified as described [CITATION_1] . The RNA was labelled at its 5Ј-OH with 32 P (as above) and annealed with the complementary DNA strand. Hydrolysis of the DNA was also tested by 5Ј-labelling of this strand. In these experiments diethylpyrocarbonatetreated water and RNase-free reagents were used.",
